## 2. Relationship Summary

| Relationship | Cardinality | Notes |
|--------------|-------------|-------|
| roles вҶ’ users | 1 : N | Each user has exactly one role. |
| users вҶ’ farms | 1 : N | A farmer/cooperative user can register multiple farms. |
| locations вҶ’ farms | 1 : N | Each farm belongs to one state/district. |
| farms вҶ” crops | M : N (via `farm_crops`) | A farm can grow multiple crops across seasons; a crop can be grown on many farms. |
| crops вҶ’ yield_records | 1 : N | Historical yield rows per crop. |
| locations вҶ’ yield_records | 1 : N | Historical yield rows per location. |
| farms вҶ’ predictions | 1 : N | A farm can have multiple predictions over time (per crop/season). |
| users вҶ’ auth_audit_log | 1 : N | Every login/register attempt is logged. |

## 3. Design Notes

- `users.role_id` drives RBAC checks in `backend/app/core/security.py`.
- `yield_records.source` distinguishes FAOSTAT/USDA/Kaggle provenance so preprocessing can apply source-specific cleaning rules.
- `predictions` table is defined now (Milestone-1) but populated starting Milestone-2 once the ML service exists вҖ” this avoids a schema migration later.
- UUID primary keys (`users`, `farms`, `predictions`) are used for entities exposed via public APIs to avoid sequential ID enumeration; `SERIAL`/`BIGSERIAL` is used for internal reference/log tables where enumeration risk is irrelevant.
- The Milestone-1 `POST /api/v1/onboarding` endpoint conceptually writes to `users` + `farms` + `farm_crops` in one transaction; today it's simulated with in-memory dicts (see `system-architecture.md` В§8) using the exact same field names, so swapping in real DB writes later is a drop-in change.